README for xls2csv.py
Python Script to Convert Microsoft Excel XLS Files to Comma-Separated Values (CSV) Files.

Usage: python xls2csv.py my_data.xls

The script will convert my_data.xls to CSV and output to the file my_data.csv.

-or even better-

for F in *.xls; do echo "$F"; python xls2csv.py "$F"; done

To convert all XLS files within a directory.

Note:

You can optionally specify and datetime columns in the 'datecolumns' array near the beginning of the script, and the script will convert them to a standard datetime format rather than the Excel integer for the datetime value.

